-{"id":"frankenjax-8wvy","title":"ReduceWindow trace panics on zero stride","description":"[HIGH] crates/fj-trace/src/lib.rs still has a loose ReduceWindow shape-inference path that parses window_dimensions/window_strides with filter_map and never rejects zero. Runtime eval_reduce_window was hardened in fj-lax, but trace inference was not. Repro: create a TraceContext with one rank-1 F64 input shaped [3], call process_primitive(Primitive::ReduceWindow, &[input], params) with window_dimensions=\"2\", window_strides=\"0\", padding=\"same\". Expected: Err(TraceError::ShapeInferenceFailed or InvalidPrimitiveParam) matching fj-lax runtime rejection. Actual: line 1761 reaches input_dim.div_ceil(stride) with stride == 0 and panics in debug/test builds. The same parser also silently drops malformed stride/window tokens instead of rejecting them, so fix should use strict parsing, require lengths equal rank, require positive windows/strides, and add trace regression coverage for zero, malformed, and short params.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T12:32:01.533515421Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T12:32:01.533515421Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenjax-8wvy","title":"ReduceWindow trace panics on zero stride","description":"[HIGH] crates/fj-trace/src/lib.rs still has a loose ReduceWindow shape-inference path that parses window_dimensions/window_strides with filter_map and never rejects zero. Runtime eval_reduce_window was hardened in fj-lax, but trace inference was not. Repro: create a TraceContext with one rank-1 F64 input shaped [3], call process_primitive(Primitive::ReduceWindow, &[input], params) with window_dimensions=\"2\", window_strides=\"0\", padding=\"same\". Expected: Err(TraceError::ShapeInferenceFailed or InvalidPrimitiveParam) matching fj-lax runtime rejection. Actual: line 1761 reaches input_dim.div_ceil(stride) with stride == 0 and panics in debug/test builds. The same parser also silently drops malformed stride/window tokens instead of rejecting them, so fix should use strict parsing, require lengths equal rank, require positive windows/strides, and add trace regression coverage for zero, malformed, and short params.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T12:32:01.533515421Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T14:38:35.845165570Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T14:38:35.843456975Z","close_reason":"Fixed: strict parsing with validation for window_dimensions/window_strides length==rank and positive values. Added 5 regression tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
