 {"id":"frankenjax-8xyn","title":"Vectorize BatchTrace expand-dims batching","description":"BatchTrace currently handles expand_dims through the generic per-element passthrough path. Add a direct batching rule that shifts logical axes past the leading batch axis, preserves scalar/tensor semantics, and avoids the O(batch) fallback loop.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T14:20:31.236695794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T14:31:20.656041047Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T14:31:20.654066698Z","close_reason":"Vectorized BatchTrace expand_dims batching while preserving logical-axis shape semantics.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
